						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Jagasian wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I think that a wide spread means for people to be able to play ROMs on a real NES or Famicom will push emulators to become even more accurate, as people realize there are still differences when playing a ROM on a real NES versus an emulator.</div>
<br />
<br />Actually, the biggest differences are in the mapper emulation, as far as I can see.  Even the MMC3 hasn't been fully 100% accurately emulated yet.  Since the PowerPak isn't using a real MMC3 for it's mapper 4 emulation, I can imagine that it too will not be 100% accurate.
<br />
<br />The good thing about the PowerPak is that it doesn't need to emulate things outside the game cart.  But there are and will be many bugs to fix inside the PowerPak in the foreseeable future.
<br />
<br />But it still is a great development tool nevertheless.</div>

