						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">dvdmth wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">A developer working on an MMC3 game would like to know whether or not his work will function on real MMC3 hardware.</div>
<br />
<br />Developing an MMC3 (real MMC3) game sounds like a highly impractical move to me, anyways.  I would really advise against it.  The only source of MMC3 chips is existing carts, and getting to those would involve a whole lot of desoldering and/or rewiring.  What's more, is that there's several revisions of the chip.
<br />
<br />I never understood why people want to write new programs using the MMC chips (besides the convenience).  Sounds like the road to madness. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

